reater}μ{\textless}i/{\textgreater}m (with the E-ELT) and a contrast of {\textasciitilde}10{\textless}sup{\textgreater}-7{\textless}sup/{\textgreater} will enable high-resolution spectroscopy and the search for molecular signatures, including H{\textless}sub{\textgreater}2{\textless}sub/{\textgreater}O, O{\textless}sub{\textgreater}2{\textless}sub/{\textgreater}, and CO{\textless}sub{\textgreater}2{\textless}sub/{\textgreater}. The observation of thermal phase curves can be attempted with the {\textless}i{\textgreater}James Webb {\textless}i/{\textgreater}Space Telescope, thanks to a contrast of 2 × 10{\textless}sup{\textgreater}-5{\textless}sup/{\textgreater} at 10 {\textless}i{\textgreater}μ{\textless}i/{\textgreater}m. Proxima b will also be an exceptional target for future IR interferometers. Within a decade it will be possible to image Proxima b and possibly determine whether the surface of this exoplanet is habitable.},
