Trace elements in Emperor seamount olivines indicate magmatism sampled an increasing proportion of pyroxenite through timeHigher than mantle Br/Cl and I/Cl in the younger seamounts indicate that the pyroxenite contains a subducted volatile componentHelium isotope variations indicate that Hawaiian plume magmatism also sampled primitive material derived from the deep mantle},
